  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my brother and I and my father went to the synagogue every Saturday and all the holidays.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I-- my upbringing was Orthodox, following in the footsteps of my father, but not to the degree that he was brought up.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now when we arrived in Spain, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I-- after a few weeks, always speaking French in in Barcelona, which many people understood, because of the-- of the Catalan, a dialect spoken in Catalunya, a province bordering on France, which made it easier for me, and of course, easier for my father to start establishing business relations.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] A month, or maybe two month after I had arrived in Spain, I went to see the dean of the University of Barcelona, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] trying to find out whether I could continue my studies of medicine at the University of Barcelona.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To my deep regret, I was told that that was impossible.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Western European countries, including Germany, never recognized diplomas, not even high school diplomas, of-- obtained in Spain, because Spain culturally and as far as education was concerned was by far not up to the level of other Western or middle-- middle European countries.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Therefore, Spain retaliated by not recognizing any diplomas or high school diplomas obtained in those countries.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the dean told me, if you want to study medicine here, your diplomas are worth nothing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the first thing to do is you will have to go to-- to high school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You will have to learn Spanish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you will have to earn your high school diploma again by when you master the language.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
